org.phoenixbioinformatics.proxy.model
Class Registration

java.lang.Object
  org.phoenixbioinformatics.proxy.model.Registration
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Registration
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A Data Transfer Object containing shared elements relating to registrations in TAIR, including basic subscription information as well as ABRC-related registration information, which is all optional.

Author:
Robert J. Muller

createPerson

private void createPerson(java.lang.String username,
                          java.lang.String password,
                          java.lang.String email,
                          java.lang.String firstName,
                          java.lang.String lastName,
                          java.sql.Timestamp expirationDate,
                          boolean autorenew)
Create a TAIR Person (including community) in the subscription. The method creates the person in the database and sets the business object data member of this class to the result.

Parameters:
username - the user's login username
password - the user's password
email - the person's email
firstName - the person's first name (optional)
lastName - the person's last name (required but uses username if null)
expirationDate - the date on which the subscription expires
autorenew - whether the user has set up autorenew on the subscription
